    <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock screensteps-wrapper--introduction screensteps-wrapper">
  <div id="text-content_239C8A90-D247-0137-7DD5-0E63FF21C970" class="text-block-content">
    <p>You can embed images in the Rich Content Editor. Image files can be uploaded from your computer or added using a URL. You can also <a href="/t5/Student-Guide/How-do-I-embed-images-from-Canvas-into-the-Rich-Content-Editor/ta-p/328" target="_blank">embed images from your course and user files</a>.</p>
<p>Several features in Canvas support the Rich Content Editor, including Announcements, Assignments, Discussions, Pages, and Quizzes.</p>
<p><strong>Note: </strong>You can embed a variety of image file types. Learn what <a href="/t5/Student-Guide/What-types-of-media-files-can-I-upload-in-Canvas-as-a-student/ta-p/528" target="_blank">types of image files you can embed</a>.</p>
  </div>
</div>

